<h1 class= "heading">Rules, Tips & Tricks</h1>
<div class="howtoplay">
  <p>1. Blackjack starts with players making bets.</p>
  <p>2. New accounts start with free $5000 chips. When a player is broke, the game will add $1000 chips to there balance chips.</p>
  <p>3. Dealer deals 2 cards to the players and two to himself (1 card face up, the other face down).</p>
  <p>4. Blackjack card values: All cards count their face value in blackjack. Picture cards count as 10 and the ace can count as either 1 or 11. Card suits have no meaning in blackjack. The total of any hand is the sum of the card values in the hand.</p>
  <p>5. Players must decide whether to stand, hit, surrender, double down, or split.</p>
  <p>6. The dealer acts last and must hit on 16 or less and stand on 17 through 21.</p>
  <p><strong>7. Players win when their hand totals higher than dealerâ€™s hand, or they have 21 or less when the dealer busts (exceeds 21).</strong></p>
  <p>8.Remember practice makes perfect, There is an art to playing BlackJack successfully, and knowing when to Hit, Split, Double and Stand comes only with practice.</p>
